Package dog.giraffe.threads

Abstractions and helper methods to define asynchronous computations.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AsyncFunction<T,​U>
    Asynchronous form of Function.
    AsyncSupplier<T>
    Asynchronous form of Supplier.
    Batch<T>
    A Batch represents a large number of tasks to be run.
    Continuation<T>
    A block of code that waits for the completion of a computation.
    Continuations.IntForks<T>
    Decomposition of a list of computations.
    Executor
    Executors accept tasks for execution.
    ParallelSearch<T,​U>
    Searches an interval for an element in parallel.
    SleepProcess<T>
    An asynchronous computation that waits for an external event.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AsyncJoin
    Waits synchronously for an asynchronous computation.
    BatchRunner
    Schedules tasks of a Batch for execution.
    Continuations
    Helper methods to compose asynchronous computations.
    SingleThreadedExecutor
    An Executor with no threads of its own.
    SingleThreadedJoin<T>
    Waits non-blocking for an asynchronous computation.
